!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

merciful /ˈmɜːsɪfʊl/

1. ADJ If you describe God or a person in a position of authority as merciful , you mean that they show kindness and forgiveness to people. (上帝或掌权者)仁慈的; 宽厚的 

例： We can only hope the court is merciful. 我们只能寄希望于法庭的宽大处理了。 

2. ADJ If you describe an event or situation as merciful , you mean that it is a good thing, especially because it stops someone's suffering or discomfort. 令人解脱的 

例： Eventually the session came to a merciful end. 这次开庭终于有了一个令人解脱的结果。

</div>

